ysician)|John Latham]]<ref>[http://www.aim25.ac.uk/cats/8/7158.htm AIM25 text-only browsing: Royal College of Physicians: LATHAM, John (1761–1843)]. Aim25.ac.uk. Retrieved on 2010-11-26.</ref> *1794 [[Matthew Baillie]]<ref>[http://www.aim25.ac.uk/cats/8/7094.htm AIM25 text-only browsing: Royal College of Physicians: BAILLIE, Matthew (1761–1823)]. Aim25.ac.uk. Retrieved on 2010-11-26.</ref> ''On the Anatomy and Physiology of the Nervous System, in Lectures, and Observations on Medicine''<ref name="ReferenceB"/> *1795 Edward Roberts<ref name="nationalarchives.gov.uk">[http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/A2A/records.aspx?cat=113-portrait&cid=-1&Gsm=2008-06-18#-1 Access to Archives]. The National Archives. Retrieved on 2010-11-26.</ref> *1796 [[John Hunter (physician)|John Hunter]]<ref name="ReferenceB"/> *1797 [[Christopher Robert Pemberton]]<ref name="nationalarchives.gov.uk"/> *1798 [[Paggen William Mayo]]<ref>''Dictionary of National Biography'' article on Mayo.</ref> *1799 [[Richard Powell (physician)|Richard Powell]], ''Observations on the bile and its diseases''<ref name="Published as a book"/> *1800 Algernon Frampton<ref name="ReferenceB"/> }}
