{{Infobox University |motto = Pohjoista tekoa |mottoeng = The Northern Factor |image_name = |name = Lapland University of Applied Sciences (UAS) |native_name = [[:fi:Lapin ammattikorkeakoulu|Lapin ammattikorkeakoulu (AMK)]] |former_names = [[Kemi-Tornio University of Applied Sciences|Kemi-Tornio UAS]] and [[Rovaniemi University of Applied Sciences|Rovaniemi UAS]] |established = 2014 |type = [[Public university|Public]] |rector = Martti Lampela |vice_rector = Reijo Tolppi |budget = EUR 43 million |staff = 560 (2014) |students = 5618 (2014) |city = [[Kemi]], [[Tornio]], [[Rovaniemi]] |province = [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]] |country = [[Finland]] |website = {{URL|www.lapinamk.fi/en}} }}
''' Lapland University of Applied Sciences''' (Lapland UAS) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[Ammattikorkeakoulu|University of applied sciences]] located in [[Kemi]] , [[Tornio]] and [[Rovaniemi]]. It was founded on January 1, 2014 as a merger between [[Rovaniemi University of Applied Sciences]] and [[Kemi-Tornio University of Applied Sciences]]. The merger carried over all the features of the previous organisations.
==History == '''Kemi-Tornio University of Applied Sciences''' was established in 1992. '''Rovaniemi University of Applied Sciences''' was established in 1996. Together with the [[University of Lapland]], they were and the new '''Lapland University of Applied Sciences''' is part of the [[Lapland University Consortium]].
Kemi and Tornio are situated in the [[Lapland (Finland)|Finnish Lapland]], close to the Swedish border on the [[Gulf of Bothnia]] and Rovaniemi is situated further north and inland close to the arctic circle.
