{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} {{BLP sources|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox Officeholder |honorific-prefix = [[The Honourable]] |name = Lisle Snell |honorific-suffix = |order = |office = [[Chief Minister of Norfolk Island]] |term_start = 20 March 2013 |term_end = 17 June 2015 |predecessor = [[David Buffett]] |successor = Office abolished |constituency = |majority = |birth_date = |birth_place = [[Norfolk Island]] |death_date = |death_place = |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality = [[File:Flag of Norfolk Island.svg|22px|border]]Norfolk Islander |spouse = |partner = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married--> |relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = |occupation = Politician, tour guide |profession = |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |religion = |signature = |signature_alt = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Lisle Denis Snell''' is a Norfolk Island politician, who from 20 March 2013 until 17 June 2015 was the final [[Chief Minister of Norfolk Island]]. He also served as Minister for Tourism. Both offices were abolished, along with the [[Legislative Assembly of Norfolk Island]] in 2015 by the [[Government of Australia]].
Snell is a [[Pitcairn]] descendant.<ref>http://www.norfolkislandgovernment.com/legislativeassembly/officeofthespeaker.html</ref> In 2013 he stated he believed Norfolk Island could become Independent of Australia.<ref>http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=11147246</ref>
Before entering politics, Snell was a tour guide.<ref>http://www.thepeerage.com/p15663.htm#i156623</ref>
