'''Professorial Lecturer''' is an alternative term for part-time [[professors]]{{clarification needed|date=January 2018}} at certain prestigious{{clarification needed|date=January 2018}} universities such as the London School of Economics, the George Washington University, Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health. The title of the professorial lecturer is used by institutions for professors who do not pursue teaching as their full-time profession but and have expertise in their respective fields. 

